getFirstOwner

IPSTypedPrincipal getFirstOwner()
                                throws SecurityException
Get the first owner principal found in the entry set. The search is in no particular order.

Returns:
first entry that has owner permission on the ACL.
Throws:
SecurityException - if ACL does not have t least one entry with owner permission, which will not happen in a properly initialized ACL.

createEntry

IPSAclEntry createEntry(String name,
                        IPSTypedPrincipal.PrincipalTypes type)
Create a new ACl entry without adding it to the ACL. The created entry must be added to the ACL using Acl.addEntry(java.security.Principal, java.security.acl.AclEntry) for it to be part of the ACL. This will not check for the name and type conflict with existing entries. No permissions are set for the entry.

Parameters:
name - name of the entry or principal, must not be null or empty.
type - principal type, one of the enumerations IPSTypedPrincipal.PrincipalTypes, must ot be null.
Returns:
new ACL entry, never null.
